# Kosy — Project Context

## Overview

Kosy is a **C++23** and **Python 3.14+** codebase for math-focused interview problems and experiments. The license is **MIT**. C++/Python interop uses **nanobind**. Builds are **CMake**-based (not single-config Make); **Ninja** is the expected generator via **CMake Presets**.

## Technical Requirements

| Area | Requirement |
| ---- | ----------- |
| C++ standard | C++23; GNU extensions may be enabled (`CMAKE_CXX_EXTENSIONS`) |
| Python | 3.14+; managed with **uv** |
| Build | CMake ≥ 3.31, Ninja |
| C++ formatting | clang-format 22+ (Microsoft base style) |
| Python formatting / lint | ruff, pyright |
| C++ tests | doctest |
| Python tests | pytest |

## C++ Dependencies (typical)

| Package | Role |
| ------- | ---- |
| doctest | Unit testing |
| spdlog | Logging |
| cxxopts | CLI parsing |
| Matplot++ | Plotting |
| nanobind | Python bindings |
| OpenMP | Parallelism (where used) |

Declared and pinned via **CPM** in `cmake/third_party` (see project CMake).

## Python Dependencies (typical)

Core stacks include **NumPy**, **SciPy**, **Matplotlib**, **Numba**, **Cython**, **nanobind**, **PyQt6**, **Loguru**, plus dev tools in `pyproject.toml` (ruff, pyright, pytest). Lock with **uv**.

## Build Commands

| Step | Command |
| ---- | ------- |
| Configure | `cmake --preset <preset>` |
| Build | `cmake --build out/build/<preset>` |
| Test (CTest) | `ctest --test-dir out/build/<preset>` |
| Python env | `uv sync` |
| Python tests | `uv run pytest` |

Presets: `linux-gcc-x64`, `linux-clang-x64`, `darwin-gcc-arm64`, `darwin-clang-arm64`, `windows-msvc-x64`.

## CMake Cache Options (selected)

| Variable | Meaning |
| -------- | ------- |
| `KOSY_BUILD_TESTING` | Enable Kosy/CTest testing targets |
| `KOSY_ENABLE_INSTALL` | Emit install rules and versioned output names |
| `BUILD_TESTING` | Standard CTest master switch |
| `CMAKE_UNITY_BUILD` | Unity builds |
| `BUILD_SHARED_LIBS` | Shared vs static |
| `CMAKE_EXPORT_COMPILE_COMMANDS` | `compile_commands.json` for IDEs |
| `KOSY_SOVERSION` | SOVERSION for shared installs |

## CMake Helpers

Defined in `cmake/utils.cmake`:

- **`kosy_cxx_library`**: `NAME`, `SRCS`, `HDRS`, `DEPS`, `COPTS`, `DEFINES`, `LINKOPTS`; flags `PUBLIC`, `TESTONLY`, `DISABLE_INSTALL`.
- **`kosy_cxx_module`**: C++ modules via `IXXS` and related target properties.
- **`kosy_cxx_test`**: Test executable with doctest/cxxopts/Matplot++ and `add_test`.

